commitResults.messageTitle: Implement skeletal version that only echoes output
commitResults.messageBody:
Changed the logo, and added a few functions to format system output
to stdout. Main function now also reads in and echoes input, and
exits when "bye" is entered. It will also print a goodbye message.

firstly, created a constructor for Duke to make it easier to hold
state/variables. Also made some of the utility functions non-static.

added the `add` and `list` features. Uses an arraylist to store and
display strings input by the user. Created the functions `addItem`
and `printList` to carry this out.

minor fix: the indent function was not working properly for strings
with multiple lines.

note: will start using conventional commits style messages for
future commits.

Added a new class `task` to keep track of tasks. Also replaced the
ArrayList<String> items with an ArrayList<Task>. Task can be pretty
printed with toString.

Added mark as done feature: Duke will look for strings beginning
with `done ` and parse the rest of the string into an int idx.
The task with index idx will be marked as done.
TODO: add error handling for strings with wrong formatting.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor(Task): Refactor into Task + Todo classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Made Task an abstract class to facilitate future additions.
Each Task subclass now has an identifier which is prepended to
toString. The Todo class is a concrete implementation which
behaves similarly to the old Task class.

commitResults.messageTitle: Feat(Task): Add Deadline and Event classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Added deadline and event classes which extend task.
Both classes have a new string parameter `time` to be set in the
constructor. This `time` string will be pretty printed in toString.

commitResults.messageTitle: Feat: Implement todo, event, deadline features (Level-4)
commitResults.messageBody:
Added the above commands, parsing is done using very simple string
operations, but should suffice for our purposes.

Factored out the function `parseAndRun` from the `run` function in
Duke. This function should be further refactored in future updates.

Fixes: fixed minor string formatting issues in the event/deadline
classes. Also made the `addItem` message more verbose.

commitResults.messageTitle: Test: Add automated text UI testing
commitResults.messageBody:
Added input+expected files, and modified run test script to compile
all .java files in the source folder.

Todo: use a proper snapshot test utility. Manually testing like this
is painful.

Added the custom exception class, with the nested enum of error
codes. Enum is great for this use case.

Todo: actually use this exception in Duke.java

Duke now uses DukeExceptions to handle errors. Each exception
will have a default message. In Duke.run, we catch these
exceptions, print the message, and resume normal functions.

Also updated the snapshot tests since the error messages changed.

TODO: the code is getting very unwieldy. Really need to refactor
soon.

Added a delete feature. Implemenation is trivial since we are
already using an ArrayList, so a new function was added to
invoke the list's remove method.

commitResults.messageTitle: Test: Update text ui tests to last commit
commitResults.messageBody:
UI tests did not include the delete feature. Added a few lines
to test for this.

1. Created a TaskList class to manage task list related operations.
Moved the `markItem` and `deleteItem` methods from Duke there.

2. Created the Command enum and CommandExecutable functional
interface. each command will have a `match` and `dispatch` method
to respectively handle matching and executing the command.
There are many other nontrivial details that will be elaborated
on in the docs (coming soon).

3. Created the parser class to handle parsing/matching of the
input strings from the scanner and the commands.

4. Moved small misc functions out to Util class. These functions deal
mainly with reusable printing operations. Will change this to a full
blown UI class in the future.

Previously matcher returned `null` for failed matches as a
pseudo-maybe (haskell maybe) value. Replaced this with an
actual optional value.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix(Task): Remove unicode ticks and crosses
commitResults.messageBody:
Task was using unicode characters for printing that misbehaved
sometimes (especially if the locale was changed). Replaced this with
the classic `[ ]` for 'unchecked' and `[X]` for 'checked' statuses.

The new Storage class will use the Gson library to serialize/
deserialize the TaskList to and from a String respectively.

Created custom (de)serializers to deal with the polymorphic Task
objects.
Added a new public method `getItemsList` to TaskList to allow us
to insert new tasks directly without using the setter commands
(which print to stdout).

TODO: Find a 'smarter' way to create the TaskList object without
exposing the private ArrayList. Possibly add a new overloaded
constructor (which takes in a List).

TODO: Complete the functionality (save/load from a file), and
write some tests.

commitResults.messageTitle: Feat: Add Save and Load Features
commitResults.messageBody:
Completed the save/load from file features.

Added 2 new  DukeExceptions for file io exceptions.

Added a new constructor to TaskList so we don't have to mainpulate
the internal ArrayList directly.

TODO: Add tests.

TODO: Creating a new DukeException requires writing a bit too much
boilerplate. Will change this in a future commit.

Saved as duke.json instead of test.json. Saving as test.json
does not seem very professional.

Added basic support for dates using java's LocalDate class.
Also refactored out TimeTask from deadline and event.

commitResults.messageTitle: Feat: Add date support for Storage class
commitResults.messageBody: Modified Storage class to work with the new dates.

Previously a new DukeException was created like this:
`throw new DukeException(DukeException.ERRORCODE)` which much
longer than it should be.

Added a new static convenience function to DukeException.Error
`create` that returns a new DukeException from that error code.

Also updated code to use this new function (instead of the old
way above).

Usage: `throw DukeException.ERRORCODE.create()`

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor: Create Ui class + move command lambdas
commitResults.messageBody:
1. Create Ui class to handle system i/o related function (printing,
scanner, etc). This Ui class replaces all the Util.* functions that
were being used. Ui is now passed as an argument in
CommandExecutable. Updated commands to use this argument.

2. Move command lambdas. The command lambdas (todoCommand,
listCommand etc) were strewn about in their respective classes
(Todo, Tasklist etc). Consolidated all of these commands as static
constants in a new CommandLibrary class. This will also deal with
any potential circular references.

Removed now unused Util class and resolved warnings in code (using
intelliJ).
Moved everything into their respective package.

Added testing of task classes: Todo, Event and Deadline. Tests
check if the instance is created correctly, has the correct
identifier, prints correctly, and markAsComplete works.

Added tests for Command. Added 2 helper functions to help test
whether commands: reject bad input, and match inputs correctly.
Currently only tests the TODO command. Will add more tests if I
find time.
Added checkstyle to gradle and fixed some minor issues.

commitResults.messageTitle: Docs: Add JavaDocs to all public functions.
commitResults.messageBody:
Wrote brief JavaDocs for all public functions. There were several
functions that should not have been private, and their access control
was modified according to their needs.

commitResults.messageTitle: Chore: Change access modifiers for some classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Some classes are only accessed by their package and have been set
to package-private.

commitResults.messageTitle: docs: Add JavaDocs to public classes
commitResults.messageBody: Added brief descriptions for each public class.

Added find command to filter and print TaskList. Made a getter in
Task to enable searching. Refactored TaskList's toString function
into a static enumerateItems function that is reused for the find
command.

Reformatted 1 line of imports.

CheckStyle's MissingJavadocType (looks for missing JavaDoc headers
for classes) is also flagging JUnit Test classes. Changed the
severity for this check to Warning since there's no other way
around this.

Command lambdas are only accessed within the Command package, so
theres no need for them to be public. Changed them to package
private.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor: Factored out Cli class from Ui
commitResults.messageBody:
To facilitate creation of the new GUI, factored out Cli as an
implementation of the Ui interface, which the new GUI component
should implement.

First iteration of working GUI. The new class GuiHelper is a
container for messages to and from duke. Pretty much a workaround
to let us reuse the existing code by implementing the Ui interface.

TODO: fix the problem where input/output text gets cut off, and
maybe add some styling

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Wrap long messages in GUI
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, long messages in the GUI were cut off. Added a function
to split the message up into chunks that can be displayed properly
one at a time.

commitResults.messageTitle: Docs: Add JavaDocs to new GUI classes
commitResults.messageBody: Also added to some other classes with missing JavaDocs.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Text in GUI displaying incorrectly
commitResults.messageBody:
Changed some properties in the fxml files to allow the text Labels to
automatically resize when the text is overrun. We don't need to split
up the messages any more.

Some JavaDocs were in a TODO state. Filled in docs for those.

Also removed an unused import.

Fixed styling issues according to CheckStyle. Mostly changing
constant names to UPPER_SNAKE_CASE and adding @Override annotations.

Screenshotted the ASCII face for the CLI and saved it as an image for
Duke. Also increased the size of the image displayed.

Add several assertions in the code. Note that most of the code does
not have many assumptions (apart from variables being non-null), and
the only place I've found they're relevant is in the Ui classes.

More non-null assertions may be useful when the variable passed is
not being used immediately, e.g. in constructors.

Added some non-null assertions where they may be useful, e.g. in
constructors. Also removed some assertions where they won't, i.e.
in functions where an error will be thrown immediately if the
variable passed is null.

Renamed several variables and methods according to suggestions from
PR review.
Deserializer was violating SLAP. Factored out a helper method.

Changed the code to use apache commons-cli. Rather not reinvent the
wheel.
Use error/help messages generated by commons-cli.

Added a new context class that contains the TaskList and Ui from
duke. Easier to pass this around. This class is pretty much a record
type from sane languages.

Added basic functionality for macros (barely working). Many important
things are still missing (see todos below).

TODO: add JavaDocs

TODO: clean up code using checkstyle

TODO: handle exceptions dealing with new macro creation

commitResults.messageTitle: Feat: Add exceptions to macro classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Now throws new DukeExceptions when a macro definition has the
wrong format, and when macro execution encounters an error halfway
through execution.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Fix error reporting for macros
commitResults.messageBody:
Renamed DukeParseException to DukeCustomException to allow it to
be used in other places.

Errors that happen halfway in a macro were not being displayed
properly. This is due to the DukeCustomException's extraMessage
being overwritten. Fixed this by only allowing extraMessage to be
assigned when it is null.

commitResults.messageTitle: Style: Clean up issues using CheckStyle.
commitResults.messageBody: Cleaned up formatting issues and added copious JavaDocs.
Forgot to add this in last push.

According to the demands of the extension, there should also be
single letter shorthands for the commands. Added default macros to
fulfill this.

Stopped the error message from printing "The following commands were
executed successfully..." when no commands were successful. Did the
same for the unsuccessful commands.
